The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, announced that President Obama will be traveling to Camp David on Sunday and will return to the White House on Monday. He also mentioned that the President called former President Nelson Mandela to congratulate him on the 20th anniversary of his release from prison. In the week ahead, the President will visit a jobs training center, meet with King Juan Carlos of Spain, and meet with the Dalai Lama. He will also deliver remarks at a fundraiser for Senator Bennet in Denver and attend a DNC fundraiser in Las Vegas. The Press Secretary also discussed the President's support for a bipartisan jobs bill and his stance on the "don't ask, don't tell" policy.